And so unusual or mad behavior, behavior that's very disturbing, and atypical-- now there's debates about all of this. And so, for example, some people have argued that everything that we call psychiatric disorders is nothing but the labels we give to behaviors that we find uncomfortable or unproductive. OK? It's nothing but that. It's just variation.
